							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/v...php?t=6791" target="_blank">www.therunes.net/forums/v...php?t=6791</a>
<br />

<br />
Hmm cant get the link to work from here so I will pate the pertinent infos.  The credit must go to keitra.  Here is the info she posted.
<br />
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
"I've been trying to figure this out for days, finally i realized that you HAD to emote first: 
<br />

<br />
/yawn ; gsay Mezzing %T 
<br />

<br />
then i tried the /useability command, and it worked! 
<br />

<br />
hrmm, so i started trying things and came up with this.... 
<br />

<br />
/yawn ; useability Fascinate ; gsay Mezzing %T 
<br />

<br />
or more generically: 
<br />

<br />
/&lt;&lt;emote&gt;&gt; ; useability &lt;&lt;exact name of skill or spell&gt;&gt; ; gsay &lt;&lt;message&gt;&gt; 
<br />

<br />
the emote HAS to be first or it wont work. 
<br />

<br />
I also play a cleric and use: 
<br />

<br />
/comfort ; useability Minor Arch Healing ; gsay Big Heal on %T! 
<br />

<br />
I've since removed fascinate from my hotbar and replaced it with that macro 
<br />

<br />
have fun!
<br />

<br />
Edited for Spelling!
<br />
_________________</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
